race.comment: Looks like a good race for DUOMO (5). Showed ability in his first campaign, including a fresh-up placing. Was gelded during the spell and has trialled nicely for return. Looks a top chance in this line-up. MISHANI VISION (13) has been knocking on the door with placings in four of five runs so far. Ran on for another minor last time at this journey and looks a clear danger again. BACETTI (15) has started twice and has shown more ability than the results show. Fitter and extra trip a plus. Can improve sharply. FLYING PHOENIX (11) ran last on debut on the Sunshine Coast when well in the market. Didn't have a lot go right early and never came on but better placed here and sure to be improved.
